But to that kind of life I am prevented from urging you, for your wife stands in the way, and without her consent you cannot adopt a life of continence ; because, although you had no right to marry her after what you said at Tubunae, yet she became your wife in all inno- cence and single—mindedness, knowing nothing of your declaration. Yet would that you could persuade her to continence, so that with nothing in your way you could render unto God what you know you owe Him l But if you cannot arrange that with her, preserve at least your conjugal chastity and ask God, Who 6311 “ bring you out of your distresses‚'' 10 grant that you may be able to do sooner or later what you find impossible now. But yet, in order 10 love God, you must give up loving the world ; in your warfare (if you have still 10 be engaged in it) keep the faith and ensue peace ; use this world’s goods 10 do good deeds, and 10 obtain this world's goods do not do evil deeds —in these duties a wife is not a hindrance, or ought not to be.
